wiki.content: “Silly Watch” is yet another song focused on watches by Lil Uzi Vert. The track features Uzi in a similar, braggadocios mood to much of the first third of the album, or the “Baby Pluto” portion of the album. He raps in a cutthroat manner over a dark beat about his material wealth and sexual prowess with women. “Silly Watch” was teased countless times before its release on Eternal Atake. The track, prior to its release on the album, was known to fans as “40 Glock.” However, producer Supah Mario tweeted in a now-deleted tweet that “40 Glock doesn’t exist,” leading fans to discover that the track was actually called “Silly Watch” once Eternal Atake’s track listing was released on March 5, 2020.
